's%20lead%20authors%20and%20a%20biological%20anthropologist%20at%20Paul%20Sabatier%20University%20in%20Toulouse%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F04%2F17%2Feurope%2Feuropean-neolithic-people-ritual-sacrifice-intl-scli-scn%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNN.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20interpretations%2C%20reported%20Science%20Advances%2C%20believe%20it%20is%20a%20form%20of%20retainer%20sacrifice%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20officiants%20killed%20enslaved%20people%2C%20servants%2C%20relatives%2C%20wives%2C%20concubines%2C%20or%20others%20to%20accompany%20their%20masters%2C%20social%20superiors%2C%20or%20relatives%20into%20the%20afterlife.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22532%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pit%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6622998310c6b0cde5f13ca2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22303%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHow%20the%20first%20victim%20was%20likely%20buried%20in%20the%20pit%3Cp%3EScience%20Advances%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20women%20had%20her%20%26quot%3Blower%20limbs%20bent%20and%20a%20fragment%20of%20grindstone%20positioned%20on%20her%20skull%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20states.%20The%20grindstone%20is%20a%20symbol%20of%20agriculture%20and%20harvest%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20was%20in%20a%20prone%20position%2C%20her%20knees%20bent%2C%20%26quot%3Bwith%20her%20neck%20resting%20on%20the%20thorax%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20first%20woman.%20This%20second%20woman%20had%20%26quot%3Btwo%20pieces%20of%20grindstone%20placed%20horizontally%20on%20her%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20thought%20that%20the%20violent%20deaths%20would%20have%20left%20the%20first%20woman%20struggling%20to%20breathe%20with%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20second%20woman%20on%20her%20neck%2C%20while%20the%20second%20woman%20would%20have%20also%20struggled%20to%20breathe%2C%20possibly%20leading%20to%20cardiac%20ar