20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECities%20such%20as%20Beijing%20and%20Tianjin%20were%20also%20particularly%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECauses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20number%20of%20factors%20leading%20to%20the%20subsidence%2C%20but%20Robert%20Nicholls%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20climate%20adaptation%20at%20the%20University%20of%20East%20Anglia%2C%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20research%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fscience-environment-68844731%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20BBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20believed%20that%20water%20extraction%20was%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20the%20dominant%20reason.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22China%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6623d8e00dfb1341e9fd5730%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22681%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFlooding%20in%20Zhuozhou%20city%3Cp%3EJADE%20GAO%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20China%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20people%20living%20in%20areas%20that%20have%20been%20fairly%20recently%20sedimented%2C%20geologically%20speaking.%20So%20when%20you%20take%20out%20groundwater%20or%20you%20drain%20the%20soils%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20subside%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20resolution%20to%20the%20issue%20%26quot%3Bcould%20lie%20in%20the%20long-term%2C%20sustained%20control%20of%20groundwater%20extraction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20comment%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftyndall.ac.uk%2Fnews%2Fa-third-of-chinas-urban-population-at-risk-of-city-sinking-new-satellite-data-shows%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20published%20in%20Science%2C%20Nicholls%20warned%20that%20%26quot%3Bsubsidence%20jeopardises%20the%20structural%20integrity%20of%20buildings%20and%20critical%20infrastructure%20and%20exacerbates%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20in%20terms%20of%20flooding%2C%20particularly%20in%20coastal%20cities%20where%20it%20reinforces%20sea-level%20rise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubsidence%20already%20costs%20China%20over%207.5%20billion%20yuan%2C%20which%20is%20around%20%241.05%20billion%2C%20a%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fnearly-half-chinas-major-cities-are-sinking-researchers-say-2024-04-18%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSubsidence%2520already%2520costs%2520China%2520more%2Ceven%2520greater%2520risk%2520of%2520inundation.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20not%20confined%20to%20China%2C%20however.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20paper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpiahs.copernicus.org%2Farticles%2F372%2F189%2F2015%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%20February%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20around%206.3%20million%20square%20km%2C%20or%20around%202.4%20million%20square%20miles%2C%20of%20land%20around%20the%20world%20was%20at%20risk%20of%20subsidence%2C%20with%20Indonesia%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20affected%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParts%20of%20the%20US%20have%20also%20suffered%20from%20the%20problem%2C%20with%20more%20than%2017%2C000%20square%20miles%20of%20land%20across%2045%20states%20directly%20affected%2C%20according%20to%20the%20United%20States%20Geological%20Survey%20(USGS).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20USGS%2C%20more%20than%2080%25%20of%20the%20identified%20cases%20of%20subsidence%20in%20the%20US%20occurred%20due%20to%20the%20exploitation%20of%20underground%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20increasing%20development%20of%20land%20and%20water%20resources%20threatens%20to%20exacerbate%20existing%20land-subsidence%20problems%20and%20initiate%20new%20ones%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falmost-half-major-chinese-cities-s