g%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehe%20was%20hardly%20making%20enough%20money%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-repayment-issues-debt-relief-broken-industry-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20pay%20off%20his%20student%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20his%20other%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20Lambdin%2C%20now%2049%2C%20said%20his%20only%20option%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20was%20to%20put%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehis%20student%20loans%20on%20forbearance%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20he%20was%20not%20making%20payments%2C%20but%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-this-fall-borrowers-unpaid-interest-debt-cancellation-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20interest%20was%20still%20accumulating.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20so%20that%20I%20could%20subsist%2C%20so%20that%20I%20could%20survive%2C%26quot%3B%20Lambdin%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWith%20the%20hope%20that%20at%20some%20point%2C%20I%20would%20be%20making%20enough%20money%20that%20I%20would%20be%20able%20to%20take%20them%20out%20of%20forbearance%20and%20start%20paying%20them%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20grew%20to%20realize%20that%20the%20only%20way%20he%20could%20make%20a%20significant%20dent%20in%20his%20student%20loans%20was%20by%20switching%20careers.%20Since%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20do%20that%20because%20he%20loved%20working%20in%20music%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20keep%20his%20larger%20student%20loan%20in%20forbearance%20and%20begin%20paying%20off%20his%20smaller%20loan%20with%20a%20lower%20monthly%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%20making%20those%20payments%20until%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-payments-resume-confusion-borrowers-debt-relief-biden-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epandemic%20student-loan%20payment%20pause%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20which%20point%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20started%20making%20a%20plan%20of%20action%20to%20tackle%20the%20larger%20debt%20once%20the%20pause%20ended.%20That%20led%20them%20to%20discover%20the%20Education%20Department's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-idr-student-debt-relief-account-adjustment-biden-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone-time%20account%20adjustment%20initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20allowed%20the%20department%20to%20evaluate%20borrowers'%20accounts%20and%20update%20payment%20progress%20toward%20forgiveness%20on%20income-driven%20repayment%20plans%20and%20Public%20Service%20Loan%20Forgiveness%2C%20including%20any%20payments%20made%20during%20a%20forbearance%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20account%20adjustment%20led%20to%20a%20letter%20Lambdin%20received%2C%20reviewed%20by%20BI%2C%20from%20his%20student-loan%20servicer%20Aidvantage%20on%20January%2031%20stating%3A%20%26quot%3BCongratulations!%20The%20Biden-Harris%20Administration%20has%20forgiven%20your%20federal%20student%20loan(s)%20listed%20below%20with%20Aidvantage%20in%20full.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Lambdin%2C%20that%20letter%20meant%20his%20%24249%2C255%20outstanding%20student-loan%20balance%20was%20effectively%20wiped%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20had%20started%20to%20feel%20like%20my%20fate%20was%20being%20decided%20for%20me%20by%20the%20cold%20hand%20of%20finance%2C%26quot%3B%20Lambdin%20said%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3Band%20that%20was%20a%20weight%20that%20I%20didn't%20realize%20was%20there%20until%20it%20wasn't%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20feeling%20was%20much%20more%20like%20putting%20down%20a%20backpack%20that%20was%20really%20full%20of%20books%20that%20you%20got%20used%20to.%20And%20then%20you%20put%20it%20down%2C%20and%20you're%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20man%2C%20that%20feels%20so%20much%20better.'%20It's%20more%20like%20that%2C%20rather%20than%20sort%20of%20a%20jump-for-joy%20kind%20of%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Lambdin%20is%20still%20working%20to%20determine%20what%20exactly%20the%20relief%20will%20mean%20for%20him%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20he%20said%20that%20discussing%20retirement%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20much%20more%20present%20conversation%20now%26quot%3B%20because%20contributing%20to%20savings%20is%20viable%20after%20the%20relief.%20He%20can%20also%20begin%20to%20look%20into%20buying%20a%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Education%20Department%20continues%20to%20cancel%20student-debt%20through%20its%20one-time%20account%20adjustments%2C%20a%20process%20it%20plans%20to%20complete%20this%20summer.%20Most%20recently%2C%20the%20department%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-student-loan-forgiveness-borrowers-save-plan-pslf-debt-cancellation-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20wiped%20out%20%247.4%20billion%20in%20student%20debt%20for%20277%2C000%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20benefited%20from%20the%20adjustments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20financial%20goals%2C%20Lambdin%20said%20the%20relief%20is%20also%20allowing%20him%20the%20freedom%20to%20pursue%20some%20of%20his%20long-term%20dreams%2C%20including%20taking%20a%20sabbatical%20to%20study%20with%20his%20meditation%20teacher%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20even%20consider%20doing%20if%20we%20had%20to%20pay%20off%20student%20loans%2C%20but%20without%20them%2C%20it's%20something%20that%20I%20can%20really%20seriously%20consider%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20those%20are%20the%20kinds%20of%20things%20that%20I%20think%20get%20really%20lost%20in%20the%20monetary%20side%20of%20the%20conversation%20about%20debt%20relief.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'I've%20been%20really%20lucky'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Lambdin%20said%20he%20feels%20as%20though%20he%20earned%20the%20relief%20given%20his%20decades%20of%20payments%2C%20he%20also%20recognized%20that%20it's%20not%20that%20easy%20for%20