rve.gov%2Fpublications%2Ffiles%2Fscf23.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrew%20by%2037%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20cracks%20have%20begun%20to%20emerge.%20People's%20savings%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FPSAVERT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20fallen%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20being%20boosted%20by%20stimulus%20checks%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20spending%20options%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20credit-card%20and%20auto-loan%20delinquencies%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%20Lower-income%20households%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20likelier%20to%20be%20struggling.%20Still%2C%20on%20the%20whole%2C%20Americans%20are%20doing%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20looking%20at%20a%20consumer%20sector%20that's%20still%20in%20overall%20good%20financial%20shape%2C%26quot%3B%20Boussour%20said.%20She%20thinks%20that%20moderation%20in%20spending%20will%20soon%20be%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20though%20it's%20worth%20noting%20economists%20have%20been%20saying%20that%20for%20months%20now%20%E2%80%94%20eventually%2C%20%3Cem%3Esomething%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20to%20break%2C%20they've%20argued%2C%20but%20it's%20just%20not%20clear%20what%20or%20when%20that%20will%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20raw%20dollars%20and%20cents%2C%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20mental%20and%20emotional%20factors%20going%20into%20people's%20willingness%20to%20suck%20it%20up%20in%20the%20face%20of%20higher%20prices.%20In%20American%20culture%2C%20consumerism%20is%20one%20hell%20of%20a%20drug.%20It's%20wrapped%20up%20in%20our%20identities%2C%20how%20we%20relate%20to%20the%20world%20and%20to%20each%20other.%20Many%20of%20us%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20look%20at%20a%20problem%20or%20frustration%20and%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20can%20I%20buy%20about%20this%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClaire%20Tassin%2C%20a%20retail%20and%20e-commerce%20analyst%20at%20Morning%20Consult%2C%20told%20me%20surveys%20indicated%20that%20the%20sticker%20shock%20of%20inflation%20had%20worn%20off%2C%20meaning%20some%20of%20the%20hate%20spending%20comes%20down%20to%20resignation.%20Per%20Morning%20Consult%2C%20the%20share%20of%20people%20who%20say%20they're%20paying%20more%20for%20products%20now%20than%20they%20were%20a%20year%20ago%20is%20back%20to%202021%20levels%2C%20even%20as%20prices%20continue%20to%20climb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20largely%20just%20accepted%20that%20the%20prices%20that%20are%20in%20the%20market%20right%20now%20are%20status%20quo%2C%26quot%3B%20Tassin%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20acclimated%20to%20these%20inflated%20prices.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20level%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2024%2F03%2F29%2Fconsumer-spending-savings-yolo-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYOLO%20splurging%3C%2Fa%3E%20going%20on%20among%20a%20lot%20of%20consumers.%20They're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftraveled-us-buenos-aires-taylor-swift-concert-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuying%20tickets%20to%20see%20Taylor%20Swift%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-summer-trip-destinations-travel-spots-countries-google-flights-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebooking%20summer%20trips%20to%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20deciding%20they%20deserve%20a%20treat%20(or%20several)%20after%20living%20through%20a%20pandemic.%20People%20figure%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20if%20I%20can't%20buy%20a%20new%20home%20right%20now%20or%20upgrade%20my%20job%20or%20car%2C%20taking%20a%20vacation%20seems%20like%20a%20decent%20alternative%2C%20even%20if%20I%20am%20paying%20more%20than%20I'd%20like.%26quot%3B%20The%20consumer%20COVID%20hangover%20is%20lasting%20longer%20than%20many%20observers%20expected%2C%20in%20a%20way%20that%20opens%20up%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20this%20you-only-live-once%20attitude%20will%20last%20forever.%20If%20consumers%20hadn't%20gone%20along%20for%20the%20ride%20on%20price%20hikes%2C%20companies%20couldn't%20have%20undertaken%20them%20in%20the%20way%20they%20did.%20Financial%20products%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuy-now-pay-later-phantom-debt-hurt-consumers-us-economy-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuy%20now%2C%20pay%20later%20have%20also%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20it%20easier%20to%20buy%20something%20you%20can't%20entirely%20afford%20at%20this%20very%20minute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20what%20would%20force%20us%20to%20hit%20the%20breaking%20point%20for%20this%20degree%20of%20consumer%20spending%2C%26quot%3B%20Tassin%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20conspicuous%20consumption%20%E2%80%94%20as%20in%20buying%20goods%20and%20services%20to%20show%20off%20a%20level%20of%20status%20%E2%80%94%20is%20back%20on%20the%20rise%20among%20demographics%20that%20are%20once%20again%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpro.morningconsult.com%2Fanalysis%2Fshopping-retail-trends-new-brands%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejonesing%20to%20try%20new%20brands%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20becoming%20less%20sensitive%20to%20prices.%20While%20lower-income%20consumers%20are%20trading%20down%20from%20expensive%20name-brand%20products%20to%20cheaper%20alternatives%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20save%20money%2C%20some%20younger%20and%20higher-income%20consumers%20are%20trading%20up%20and%20shrugging%20off%20the%20higher%20costs%20that%20come%20with%20that%2C%20even%20if%20it%20irks%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20want%20to%20achieve%20a%20higher%20social%20status.%20They%20want%20to%20live%20a%20life%20that%20impresses%20others%2C%20and%20being%20part%20of%20the%20popular%20crowd%20is%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Tassin%20said.%20%26quot%3BPart%20of%20it%20is%20just%20like%2C%20'This%20is%20what%20it%20costs%20now.%20And%20yes%2C%20it's%20a%20lot%20more%20expensive%20than%20it%20used%20to%20be%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20important%20to%20me%20to%20keep%20spending.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20misalignment%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F04%2F18%2Fus%2Fgreenville-real-estate-conservatives.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople's%20stated%20attitude%20toward%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20their%20actual%20behavior%20isn't%20that%20outlandish%20%E2%80%94%20our%20intentions%20and%20emotions%20often%20don't%20match%20our%20actions.%20People%20say%20they%20want%20to%20eat%20healthy%20all%20the%20time%20and%20then%20find%20themselves%20in%20the%20ice%20cream%20aisle.%20It's%20easy%20to%20say%20you%20want%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20spending%2C%20given%20high%20prices%2C%20but%20when%20a%20friend%20asks%20whether%20you%20want%20to%20go%20shopping%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20say%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERavi%20Dhar%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20marketing%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Customer%20Insights%20at%20Yale%20School%20of%20Management%2C%20told%20me%20there's%20a%20sort%20of%20decoupling%20going%20on%20between%20people's%20current%20situations%20and%20how%20they%20feel%20about%20the%20future.%20They%20see%20a%20headline%20about%20people%20getting%20laid%20off%2C%20or%20they%20know%20there's%20a%20global%20conflict%20going%20on%2C%20so%20they%20feel%20more%20pessimistic%20about%20the%20economy%20and%20worried%20about%20costs.%20But%20when%20it%20comes%20down%20to%20actually%20paying%2C%20they%20still%20have%20a%20job%20and%20maybe%20even%20got%20a%20raise%2C%20so%20they%20pony%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20uneasy%20feelings%20about%20the%20future%20and%20how%20it%20might%20change%2C%20whereas%20expenditures%20and%20spending%20now%20is%20determined%20by%20the%20current%20state%20of%20affairs%2C%26quot%3B%20Dhar%20said.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20predictions%20have%20become%20more%20pessimistic%2C%20but%20not%20their%20behavior.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20a%20needs%20vs.%20wants%20question%20here.%20Some%20items%20are%20necessities%20%E2%80%94%20a%20home%20to%20live%20in%2C%20food%20on%20the%20table%2C%20gas%20in%20the%20car%2C%20childcare%2C%20healthcare.%20Consumers%20are%20understandably%20frustrated%20at%20the%20costs%20of%20these%20things.%20But%20in%20some%20instances%2C%20people%20conflate%20what%20is%20a%20need%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fmoney%2F24009905%2Fmoney-personal-finance-goals-expectations-needs-vs-wants-economy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat's%20a%20reasonable%20expectation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20what%20sorts%20of%20trade-offs%20they%20perhaps%20should%20make%20to%20achieve%20their%20financial%20goals.%20None%20of%20us%20%3Cem%3Ehave%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20subscribe%20to%20six%20streaming%20services%20or%20escape%20to%20a%20lavish%20weekend%20getaway%2C%20even%20if%20we%20tell%20ourselves%20that's%20what%20we%20deserve%20for%20stomaching%20the%20workday%20and%20staring%20down%20a%20grocery%20bill%20that's%20much%20higher%20than%20it%20used%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20the%20outside%2C%20that%20might%20look%20like%20a%20luxury%20but%20to%20them%20it%20says%2C%20'Hey%2C%20this%2C%20I%20need%20all%20this%20for%20my%20sanity%2C'%26quot%3B%20Dhar%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20averse%20to%20loss%2C%20and%20having%20to%20change%20their%20lifestyle%20to%20fit%20newfound%20financial%20constraints%20feels%20like%20losing.%20There's%20an%20element%20of%20stubbornness%20here%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3Eof%20course%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20dress%20in%20the%20closet%20is%20just%20fine%20to%20wear%20to%20that%20party%2C%20but%20getting%20the%20new%20one%20is%20more%20%3Cem%3Efun%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3Eexciting%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20even%20if%20the%20accompanying%20price%20tag%20is%20annoying.%20It'll%20be%20something%20interesting%20to%20complain%20about%20at%20said%20party%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReporting%20for%20this%20story%2C%20I%20heard%20from%20all%20sorts%20of%20people%20about%20their%20hate-spending%20habits.%20One%20woman%20told%20me%20she%20despised%20spending%20over%20%241%2C000%20on%20an%20iPhone%2C%20even%20as%20she%20insisted%20on%20replacing%20hers%20at%20least%20every%20two%20years%20(she%20figured%20she%20should%20have%20one%20that%20works%20%26quot%3Bawesome%26quot%3B).%20And%2C%20like%20many%20people%2C%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphone-doj-lawsuit-antitrust-green-bubble-samsung-stigma-2024-4%3Fmrfhud%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewon't%20switch%20to%20another%20brand%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20man%20said%20he'd%20really%20gotten%20into%20couponing%20and%20racking%20up%20points%20at%20his%20local%20grocery%20store%2C%20but%20sometimes%2C%20he's%20just%20got%20to%20have%20that%20bag%20of%20Doritos%2C%20even%20if%20it%20costs%20the%20price%20of%20two%20bags%20three%20years%20ago.%20People%20cited%20angrily%20buying%20dog%20toys%2C%20fancy%20chocolates%2C%20deodorant%2C%20and%20%249%20Chex%20Mix%20at%20the%20airport.%20Some%20mentioned%20doing%20more%20inevitable%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20more%20rage-inducing%20%E2%80%94%20spending%20on%20big-ticket%20items%20like%20rent.%20Upon%20reflection%2C%20I've%20realized%20I%20have%20two%20categories%20of%20expenses%20I%20love%20to%20hate%3A%20martinis%20at%20half-decent%20New%20York%20restaurants%20and%20my%20internet%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20were%20aware%20that%20many%20purchases%20were%20things%20they%20could%20go%20without.%20The%20Doritos%20guy%20knows%20he%20could%20go%20without%20the%20premium%20channels%20in%20his%20cable%20package%2C%20but%20he%20doesn't%20think%20his%20bill%20would%20come%20down%20far%20enough%20to%20warrant%20the%20sacrifice.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20my%20conversation%20with%20the%20iPhone%20lady%2C%20she%20said%20she'd%20started%20to%20wonder%20whether%20it%20might%20be%20better%20to%20wait%20to%20make%20the%20purchase%20%E2%80%94%20the%20crack%20in%20her%20screen%20would%20be%20easy%20and%20cheap%20enough%20to%20fix.%20But%20she%20doesn't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20big%20expenses%20at%20the%20moment.%20It's%20not%20like%20her%20car's%20broken%20down%2C%20so%20she'll%20probably%20go%20ahead%20and%20buy%20a%20new%20phone.%20She%20feels%20like%20it's%20an%20investment%20in%20herself.%20Hart%2C%20the%20Illinois%20writer%20with%20a%20brand-new%20Stanley%20cup%2C%20sees%20some%20of%20her%20spending%20as%20a%20way%20to%20reclaim%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20a%20choice%20in%20the%20economy%20and%20inflation%20and%20how%20that's%20affecting%20you%2C%20but%20you%20kind%20of%20have%20a%20choice%20in%20how%20much%20you%20let%20it%20alter%20your%20lifestyle%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20you're%20admitting%20defeat%20if%20you're%20just%20like%2C%20'Well%2C%20now%20it's%20just%20expensive%2C%20so%20I%20won't%20do%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20hyperconsumerist%20society%20like%20the%20one%20we%20live%20in%2C%20it's%20a%20notion%20that%20tracks.%20Maybe%20we're%20all%20angry%20spending%20soldiers%2C%20refusing%20to%20be%20deterred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhate-spending-consumers-economic-sentiment-retail-sales-inflation-gdp-growth-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713693421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661feeb110c6b0cde5f0568d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhate-spending-consumers-economic-sentiment-retail-sales-inflation-gdp-growth-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22People%20say%20the%20e